citeinfo.othercit: Venter, FJ (1990) "A Classification of Land for Management Planning in the Kruger National Park" PhD Thesis: University of Pretoria (We hope to have this thesis publically available in .pdf format soon! - gismaster)

descript.abstract: A polygon theme containing "land scapes" classifications based on: - dominant soil series - dominant woody plant species - hillslope units - landform characteristics (relief, soil, slope length, stream frequency) - rainfall for management planning and ecological studies in the Kruger National Park.
descript.purpose: For the KNP Scientific Services GIS database - for research and cartographic products. This database is intended to be extended or incorporated into a future KNP "Regional GIS" node of SANP.
descript.supplinf: Dr Venter works for SANParks in the Kruger NP under Resource Management as Manager: Aquatic Systems and is based at Phalaborwa. E-mail: freekv@parks-sa.co.za
